---
layout: layouts/base.njk
title: ""
description: "Fabrizio Palladino — UX Engineer and Front-end Developer"
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <h1 class="hero__title" data-reveal>Fabrizio Palladino</h1>
    <p class="hero__subtitle" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">UX Engineer working between interfaces and the people who use them.</p>
    <p class="hero__intro" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
      I build accessible, performant interfaces that put people first.
      I focus on design systems, front-end architecture, and making the web work for everyone.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--border">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <h2 data-reveal>What's on My Mind</h2>
    <div class="grid" style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-md);">
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="1">
        <h3 class="card__title">UX in the Kitchen</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Cooking as a behavioral lab. Mise en place, working memory, the parts a recipe quietly assumes.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="2">
        <h3 class="card__title">Field Notes</h3>
        <p class="card__text">From the day job. The small moments where a design assumption met a real user.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="3">
        <h3 class="card__title">Everyday Systems</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Non-digital interfaces: ticket gates, signage, train stations. The lens applies beyond screens.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="4">
        <h3 class="card__title">Reading the Field</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Notes on books and papers that shape how I think — Norman, Krug, Kahneman, and the quieter voices in between.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="5">
        <h3 class="card__title">Three Things</h3>
        <p class="card__text">A short recurring post. Three things I noticed this month — at work, at home, somewhere in between.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="card" data-reveal data-reveal-delay="6">
        <h3 class="card__title">Letters</h3>
        <p class="card__text">Longer essays for when an idea needs more space. Less frequent, more meditative.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-md);" data-reveal>
      <a href="/blog/" class="cta-link">Browse the blog</a>
    </p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--border">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <div data-reveal>
      <h2>About Me</h2>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-sm);">
        After studying Management of Publishing Enterprises, I fell in love with HTML, CSS, and their potential.
        That passion broadened to include everything that makes the web usable, accessible, and reliable.
      </p>
      <p style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-sm);">
        <a href="/about/" class="cta-link">Learn more about me</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section section--border">
  <div class="container container--wide">
    <h2 data-reveal>Latest Posts</h2>
    <div style="margin-top: var(--fp-space-md);">
      {% set posts = collections.blog | reverse %}
      {% if posts.length > 0 %}
        {% for post in posts %}
          {% if loop.index <= 3 %}
            <div class="post-list__item" data-reveal>
              <a href="{{ post.url }}" class="post-list__link">
                <h3 class="post-list__title">{{ post.data.title }}</h3>
                <p class="post-list__meta">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</p>
                {% if post.data.description %}
                  <p class="post-list__description">{{ post.data.description }}</p>
                {% endif %}
              </a>
            </div>
          {% endif %}
        {% endfor %}
      {% else %}
        <p data-reveal>Blog posts coming soon.</p>
      {% endif %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
